summary: This document contains technical instructions for using FARO SCENE point cloud interactive software, likely for viewing 3D scans of a crime scene or location. It appears to be an FBI Laboratory guide for processing digital evidence, possibly related to scanning a location connected to the Epstein case.
keyFacts: Document is technical instructions for FARO SCENE point cloud software used for 3D scanning.
Instructions are from the FBI Laboratory / Operational Projects Unit.
Document references contact information for a TDDP supervisor with office and cell numbers (redacted).
Software is used for measuring and viewing 3D scan data of scenes.
Document appears to be procedural guidance for handling digital scan evidence.
